<recipeml version="0.5">
  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Vinegar Spiced Nuts</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>None</cat></categories>
      <yield>1</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>cup</unit></amt>
        <item>Granulated sugar</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>5</qty>
          <unit>tablespoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Water</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>tablespoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Vinegar</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>teaspoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Cinnamon</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>teaspoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Vanilla</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Mixed nuts or peanuts or plain salted nuts or walnuts</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Boil all together until it spins a thread. Stir in nuts until it sugars.
  Pour out on waxed paper and separate nuts with a fork. A real special treat
  for that special company!
  Posted to recipelu-digest Volume 01 Number 236 by "Diane Geary"
  &lt;diane@keyway.net&gt; on Nov 10, 1997
 
</step></directions></recipe></recipeml>
